":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A7%D9%90%D8%B1%D9%92%D8%AA%D9%8E%D9%81%D9%8E%D8%B9%D9%8E"}},"translations":null,"definition":null,"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n16157","headword_ar":"ارتفع","root":"rfE","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It became raised;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it rose: it rose high,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became high"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"elevated"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lofty:"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it became raised, upraised, uplifted,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"elevated,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it rose, from its resting-place:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and, said of a building,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it became reared, upreared,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"made high"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lofty:"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it became taken up:"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it became taken away, put away,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"removed;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it went away; after its coming"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"arriving:"},{"kind":"text","text":"thus when said of corporeal things: but when said of ideal things, it is tropically used, as it is also in many other cases, and accorded in meaning to what the case requires:] quasi-pass. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rafaEahu","text_ar":"رَفَعَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"as signifying the contr. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waDaEahu","text_ar":"وَضَعَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, K.) [See 1; first sentence.] ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It"},{"kind":"text","text":"(the water of a well)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rose, by its becoming copious:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it went away:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qlS","text_ar":"قلص"},{"kind":"text","text":":) [in which latter sense, likewise, it is said of milk in the udder; or as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it became drawn up,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"withdrawn,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"withheld:"},{"kind":"text","text":"see 1. See also a usage of this verb voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raqaA^a","text_ar":"رَقَاَ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] ―         -b3-  (tropical:)  Said of a man: see 1, voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rafuEa","text_ar":"رَفُعَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", near the end of the paragraph. ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ArtfE qadoruhu","text_ar":"ارتفع قَدْرُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"His rank became high, elevated, exalted, lofty,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"eminent"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S, TA.) ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AirotafiEo","text_ar":"اِرْتَفِعْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", said to a man entering a sittingplace, sitting-room, or assembly, means (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Advance thou:"},{"kind":"text","text":"it is not from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AirotifaAEN","text_ar":"اِرْتِفَاعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"denoting height. (TA.) ―         -b6-  See also 5. ―         -b7-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ArtfEt AlD~uHaY","text_ar":"ارتفعت الضُّحَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The morning became advanced;"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the sun became high:"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlD~uHaY","text_ar":"الضُّحَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"being originally a pl., namely, of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlD~aHowapu","text_ar":"الضَّحْوَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; [wherefore the verb is fem.;] but afterwards used as a sing. [as in the next ex. here following]. (Msb.) You say also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlD~uHaY","text_ar":"الضُّحَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taraf~aEa","text_ar":"تَرَفَّعَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  [meaning the same]. (TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ArtfE Aln~ahaAru","text_ar":"ارتفع النَّهَارُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The day became advanced, the sun being somewhat high:"},{"kind":"text","text":"a phrase said by the doctors of the law in the present day to be employed when the sun has risen the measure of a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rumoH","text_ar":"رُمْح"},{"kind":"text","text":"or more]. (S and K in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mtE","text_ar":"متع"},{"kind":"text","text":"; &c.) ―         -b8-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ArtfE Als~iEoru waA@noHaT~a","text_ar":"ارتفع السِّعْرُ وَا@نْحَطَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The price rose,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"advanced, and became low,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"abated"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) ―         -b9-  ["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ArtfEwA","text_ar":"ارتفعوا"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  They"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"removed"},{"kind":"text","text":"from, or to, a place. ―         -b10-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ArtfE Eanohu","text_ar":"ارتفع عَنْهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", said of a disease, pain, an affliction, and the like, (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It quitted him; became withdrawn from him."},{"kind":"text","text":"] ―         -b11-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aln~aqiyDaAni laA","text_ar":"النَّقِيضَانِ لَا"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yajotamiEaAni walaA yarotafiEaAni","text_ar":"يَجْتَمِعَانِ وَلَا يَرْتَفِعَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"What are termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nqyDAn","text_ar":"نقيضان"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cannot be coexistent in the same thing, nor simul taneously nonexistent in the same thing"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; as existence itself and nonexistence, and motion and rest. (Kull pp. 231 and 232.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ArtfEhu","text_ar":"ارتفعهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see 1; first sentence."}],"source_refs":[]}]},"classical_definitions":null}